concepts.notes:
**Pattern from Lab03B:**
```java
public static String getAttribute(char c) {
    if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') return "Identifier";
    else if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') return "Identifier";
    else if (c == '+' || c == '-' || c == '*' || c == '/') return "Operator";
    else if (c == ';') return "Symbol";
    return null; // unrecognised
}
```

This is called for every non-whitespace character in the input string.

